text: Eider Merino Cortazar (born 2 August 1994) is a Spanish professional racing cyclist, who currently rides for UCI Women's WorldTeam . Prior to joining the in 2018, Merino rode for five years with the team. Her elder brother Igor Merino is also a professional cyclist, but is currently suspended from the sport. ==See also== * List of 2015 UCI Women's Teams and riders ==References== ==External links== * * Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:Basque cyclists Category:Spanish female cyclists Category:Sportspeople from Biscay
